
[1]adiaphorists

   ADIAPH'ORISTS, n. [Gr. indifferent.]

   Moderate Lutherans; a name given in the sixteenth century, to certain
   men that followed Melancthon, who was more pacific than Luther

   The adiaphorists held some opinions and ceremonies to be indifferent,
   which Luther condemned as sinful or heretical.
